  "title": "Torque - forces on a rotating wheel",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two blocks attached to either end of a light string that passes over a circular wheel of mass m. The block on the left has mass m sub 1, and the block on the right has mass m sub 2. The tension in the left portion of the string is T sub 1, and the tension in the right portion of the string is T sub 2. The block with mass m sub 1 is lower than the block with mass m sub 2.\" src=\"/images/493128acd0753b7c39605f5b15ee04dd.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two blocks of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub 1\"><math alttext=\"m sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub 2\"><math alttext=\"m sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> are connected by a thin string that passes over a circular wheel of mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m\"><math alttext=\"m\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>m</mi></math></span></span>, as shown. The wheel is attached to a vertical stand and rotates freely about its center. The string does not slip on the wheel and exerts forces <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 1\"><math alttext=\"T sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 2\"><math alttext=\"T sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> on the blocks. When the wheel is released from rest in the position shown, it undergoes an angular acceleration and rotates clockwise. Which of the following statements about the magnitudes of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 1\"><math alttext=\"T sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 2\"><math alttext=\"T sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span> is correct?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i4",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 1 equals T sub 2\"><math alttext=\"T sub 1 equals T sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span> because the tension in the string must always be constant within the string.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 1 equals T sub 2\"><math alttext=\"T sub 1 equals T sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span> because both blocks have the same acceleration.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 1 is less than T sub 2\"><math alttext=\"T sub 1 is less than T sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span> because <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub 1\"><math alttext=\"m sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span> is farther from the wheel than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"m sub 2\"><math alttext=\"m sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span></p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"T sub 1 is less than T sub 2\"><math alttext=\"T sub 1 is less than T sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mi>T</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mstyle></math></span></span> because an unbalanced clockwise torque is needed to accelerate the wheel clockwise.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
